{{orphan|date=December 2011}}
The '''Archaeological Society of Slovenia''' is a [[non-governmental organization]] that unites [[Slovenia|Slovene]] [[archaeologist]]s on a voluntary basis. The society organises presentations of new archaeological research, lectures and study trips, and publishes the Slovene Archaeology Society Bulletin, as well as Arheo Journal. Its members participate in international [[Academic conference|conferences]] and symposia. Every year the Award of the Archaeological Society of Slovenia is bestowed to individuals for professional achievements.<ref name="Lozny2011">{{cite book|author=Ludomir R. Lozny|title=Comparative Archaeologies: A Sociological View of the Science of the Past|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HFkueBuO-ucC&pg=PA461|date=6 April 2011|publisher=Springer Science & Business Media|isbn=978-1-4419-8225-4|pages=461–}}</ref>
== Mission ==
The society plays an important role in presenting actual issues to the public. Recently the archaeologists have been facing lack of storage places due to 50 to 100 [[archaeological site]]s researched every year, mainly on highway construction. Several tons of archaeological finds are excavated every year.
There are a few archaeological parks in Slovenia, such as [[Most na Soči]], [[Emona|Roman Emona]], the Church of St George in [[Legen]] near [[Slovenj Gradec]], Šempeter Necropolis, Rifnik Archaeological Site near [[Celje]], and [[Vranje]] near [[Sevnica]]. Most Slovene regional [[museum]]s also have a permanent archaeological exhibition.
== Recognitions == The society's award and related recognitions have been granted yearly since 1996. The award is given for lifetime achievement and for outstanding contributions to [[archaeology]]. The society also recognises the important achievements in the field of archaeology in the previous year and commemorates merited individuals by giving them honorary and worthy membership.
Previous award winners have been {{Interlanguage link multi|Janez Dular|sl|3=Janez Dular (arheolog)}} (2013),<ref>{{cite book|title=Acta archaeologica|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8uhIAQAAIAAJ|volume=61|year=2010|pages=259–}}</ref> Irena Šavel (2009),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://siol.net/trendi/svet-znanih/nagrada-arheoloskega-drustva-za-zivljenjsko-delo-ireni-savel-93309|title=Nagrada arheološkega društva za življenjsko delo Ireni Šavel|date=8 June 2009|publisher=|accessdate=16 May 2016}}</ref> {{Interlanguage link multi|Biba Teržan|sl}} (2008),<ref name="umetnostiLjubljani2007">{{cite book|author1=Slovenska akademija znanosti in umetnosti|author2=Akademija znanosti in umetnosti v Ljubljani|title=Letopis|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QME7AQAAIAAJ|volume=58-59|year=2007|language=Slovenian |pages=217–}}</ref> Mitja Guštin (2007), Mira Strmčnik Gulič (2006),<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.delo.si/kultura/dediscina/mira-strmcnik-gulic-vznemirljivost-in-pricakovanja-arheologa.html|title=Mira Strmčnik Gulič: Vznemirljivost in pričakovanja arheologa|work=www.delo.si|accessdate=16 May 2016}}</ref> Marijan Slabe (2003), Ivan Turk (2002), Nada Osmuk (2001), [[Ljudmila Plesničar Gec]] (2000), Iva Mikl Curk (1999), Paola Korošec (1998), and Stanko Pahič (1998).
