'''Shurahbil ibn Amr''' was a [[Ghassanids|Ghassanid]] governor<ref>[https://books.google.co.il/books?id=80wxCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA309&lpg=PA309&dq=Shurahbil+ibn+Amr&source=bl&ots=fHOKbb8Chg&sig=KobApnJHHuN4lz2FHfL5dAxGlAI&hl=iw&sa=X&ved=0CEYQ6AEwBmoVChMIwciq3uOoyAIVhdgaCh0MyQMt#v=onepage&q=Shurahbil%20ibn%20Amr&f=false ''War and Peace in the Life of the Prophet Muhammad'': p219]</ref> of the vassal Ghassanid confederation (authority) under the Byzantine Empire in southern [[Syria (region)|Syria region]] during the 7th century.

